baddcircuit

The diagram represents a 4-bit binary adder using only basic logic gates :

XOR: to calculate the sum without carrying.
AND: to generate the carry .
OR: to propagate the retention.
This type of setup is called a ripple carry adder : each block adds two bits and a carry, and propagates the carry to the next bit.

